Note:
Target module for tests/compiler/stage1/test_8arg_call.runa. Defines an
8-parameter function used to exercise the dotted-form qualified-call
parser fix for bug #387.
:End Note

Process called "add8" that takes a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer, d as Integer, e as Integer, f as Integer, g as Integer, h as Integer returns Integer:
    Let s be a plus b
    Set s to s plus c
    Set s to s plus d
    Set s to s plus e
    Set s to s plus f
    Set s to s plus g
    Set s to s plus h
    Return s
End Process

Note: Stand-alone entry for direct invocation of the 8-arg adder; the
Note: cross-module variant is in test_8arg_call.runa.  Returns 0 when
Note: stage1 correctly handles all eight intra-module call arguments.
Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let result be add8(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8)
    Return result minus 36
End Process
